    "created_at": "2016-09-19T17:25:21Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-09-19T17:25:21Z",
    "body": "Thanks @enlight. I've had a look at that lib and it works around this issue by checking if there's been a [number of unchecked words by the spellchecker](https://github.com/paulcbetts/electron-spellchecker/blob/7bda47a5395f599ebcb418a1f1348e9e97f16f68/src/spell-check-handler.js#L183), then uses that to infer if it should try to re-detect language and auto change the language from there.\n\nI was looking at getting more than one language spell checking at once though. Some users have been asking for suggestions in multiple languages as they quite often type bilingually \n"
