    "created_at": "2016-09-19T17:31:16Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-09-19T17:31:21Z",
    "body": "@Thomas101 I've never tested this, but I can't imagine that Chrome or even Microsoft Word does multilingual spell checking.  For one main reason I can think of.\n\nIf a word is valid in one language and invalid in another.  Is it an error?  The spell checker would have to contextually understand what language the block of test the word is in is written in.  And even then, quoting a different language would result in errors.\n\nSpell checking multiple languages at the same time will either result in an increase in false positives or ignoring real spelling mistakes.  I don't see how this could possible be implementing in a consistent and precise manner ðŸ˜¢ \n\n> Run the spellchecker over different character sets?\n\nThis however definitely seems to be some form of a bug ðŸ˜† \n"
  },
