    "updated_at": "2016-09-19T19:30:06Z",
    "body": "I agree it's a real edge case, but one that I think still has some validity. The approach I took was to setup a primary and secondary language. A correct spelling in either language falls out to a correct language and corrections can be provided for either.\n\nAfter digging through the source it looks like it falls through to `spellcheck_worditerator.cc` which calls `uscript_getCode` with the language code. This is translated into a character subset which is used for optimising the detection. There's a list of locales to language codes [here](https://opensource.apple.com/source/WebCore/WebCore-7601.3.8/platform/text/LocaleToScriptMappingDefault.cpp) so I can probably build a matrix of compatible languages using that :)\n\nCan anyone in the know confirm this?\n"
  },
