    "created_at": "2016-09-21T05:48:50Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-09-21T05:48:50Z",
    "body": "The design of spellchecker API is from Chromium and currently it can only check spell for exactly only one language. Making it support multiple languages is nice but we don't have someone familiar with spellchecking to do it, and we don't have resources for that neither, so I'm closing this as won't fix.\n\n> After digging through the source it looks like it falls through to spellcheck_worditerator.cc which calls uscript_getCode with the language code.\n\nYeah it is the code for iterating words, and you can start hacking from it.\n"
